daikon.inv.binary.sequenceString

Class SequenceString

  • Object
    • Invariant
      • BinaryInvariant
        • SequenceString
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Cloneable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    MemberString

    public abstract class SequenceString
extends BinaryInvariant
    Abstract base class for comparing String sequences to String variables. Note that the sequence must always be passed in first. An example is x is a member of a[].

      • check_modified

        public abstract InvariantStatus check_modified(String[] v1,
                                               String v2,
                                               int count)
        Presents a sample to the invariant. Returns whether the sample is consistent with the invariant. Does not change the state of the invariant.
        Parameters:
        count - how many identical samples were observed in a row. For example, three calls to check_modified with a count parameter of 1 is equivalent to one call to check_modified with a count parameter of 3.
        Returns:
        whether or not the sample is consistent with the invariant

      • add_modified

        public abstract InvariantStatus add_modified(String[] v1,
                                             String v2,
                                             int count)
        Similar to check_modified(java.lang.String[], java.lang.String, int) except that it can change the state of the invariant if necessary. If the invariant doesn't have any state, then the implementation should simply call check_modified(java.lang.String[], java.lang.String, int). This method need not check for falsification; that is done by the caller.

      • add_unmodified

        public InvariantStatus add_unmodified(String[] v1,
                                      String v2,
                                      int count)
        By default, do nothing if the value hasn't been seen yet. Subclasses can override this.
